Durban — iSimangaliso Wetland Park has provided tips on how visitors and surrounding communities can approach and behave when near elephants in a vehicle. The park also shared what visitors and communities should never do in this situation. iSimangaliso Wetland Park spokesperson Bheki Manzini said: “Rather be safe than sorry. An elephant is a formidable giant. Respect them and their space.” How to approach and behave near elephants when in a vehicle: ALWAYS: NEVER: Daily News